OL,6,FDefending the ads, both companies
OL,7,Fargued that consumers had no doubt
OL,8,Fabout the existence of such commercial
OL,9,Frelationships when they saw the
OL,10,Fendorsement within a paid-for ad taken
OL,11,Fout by a company.
OL,13,FThis expectation removed the need for
OL,14,Fthe commercial relationship to be
OL,15,Fexplicitly stated.
